  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Do questions on Quora that are non-anonymous get more distribution when posted as a follow-up to another question?",
  "response": "On Quora, the distribution of a question can be influenced by various factors, including whether it is posted as a follow-up to another question. Here's a breakdown of how this might work:\n\n1. **Visibility and Engagement**: When you post a follow-up question to an existing question, it appears in the same thread. This can increase its visibility among users who are already engaged with the original question. If the original question has a high number of views, followers, or answers, your follow-up question might benefit from this existing engagement.\n\n2. **Relevance and Context**: Follow-up questions that add meaningful context or depth to the original question can attract more attention. Users interested in the topic may be more likely to engage with your follow-up if it provides additional value or explores a new angle.\n\n3. **Non-Anonymous vs. Anonymous**: Non-anonymous questions generally receive more engagement on Quora because users can see the identity and credibility of the person asking the question. This can lead to higher visibility and more answers. When a non-anonymous follow-up question is posted, it might benefit from both the user's reputation and the context of the original question.\n\n4. **Quora's Algorithm**: Quora's algorithm considers various factors such as user engagement, topic relevance, and the user's activity on the platform. While posting a follow-up question can increase its initial visibility within the thread, the algorithm will also determine how it performs in broader searches and feeds.\n\n5. **Timing**: The timing of when you post your follow-up question can also affect its distribution. Posting when the original question is still receiving active engagement can be beneficial.\n\nIn summary, posting a non-anonymous follow-up question to another question on Quora can potentially increase its distribution due to enhanced visibility and engagement within the existing thread. However, the overall impact will depend on various factors, including the popularity of the original question, the relevance of your follow-up, and Quora's algorithmic considerations.",
